HEADWORD: Hyperpnœa
<hw>Hy`perp*n⟦oe⟧"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>"ype`r</grk> over + <?/, <?/, breath.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Abnormal breathing, due to slightly deficient
arterialization of the blood; -- in distinction from
<contr>eupn⟦oe⟧a</contr>. See <er>Eupn⟦oe⟧a</er>, and
<er>Dispn⟦oe⟧a</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hyperpyrexia</ent>⟦br⟧
